  "texts": [
    "An additional floor noise of 14 ppm is added for all simulations.",
    "We adopt the methodology described in Lustig-Yaeger et al. (2019) for the SNR calculation.",
    "The absolute difference between the 3D and 1D spectra, at which the noise is calculated, is determined first.",
    "Then, additional noise is computed using Equation 2 to account for the outof-transit baseline noise, as explained in Fauchez et al. (2022).",
    "The signal-to-noise ratio at each wavelength point, 𝑆 𝑁 𝑖"
  ]
}